{"ItemName":"Learning to Teach Online","Major":"Education ","LinkUrl":"https://www.coursera.org/course/ltto","Content":"Are you an educator, and have you ever wanted to understand more about how to design learning activities and teach effectively in fully online or blended contexts from those who have practical experience?<br><br>The Learning to Teach Online MOOC is designed to help you develop a working understanding of successful online teaching pedagogies that you can apply in your own unique teaching situations. The course provides a solid practically and pedagogically focused foundation for you to begin teaching online for the first time, or to improve the effectiveness of your existing online teaching practice if you already have experience. No matter what type of technology you are interested in exploring, the course will inform you of successful pedagogical approaches for improving your skills in designing online learning activities, assessments and resources.<br><br>The course includes a range of case studies featuring real educators in a range of different educational and disciplinary contexts, and provides proven and pragmatic advice to help you to improve your own practice. As well as discussing the benefits of online teaching for educators and students, Learning to Teach Online also acknowledges the frustrations and challenges involved, providing a range of practical strategies to overcome them. <br><br><br>","ImageUrl":"https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/5e/b5f1bb38966fa86a9d34e7a3fa6550/Screen-Shot-2013-10-17-at-3.06.00-pm.png","Short_des":"This course is designed to help educators in any sector build a practical understanding of pedagogical concepts they can apply to get started in online teaching, or to improve their existing use of educational technologies.","AuthorList":[{"author":"Simon  McIntyre"}]}